---
// How It Works Section - Simplified methodology
const layers = [
  "Problem Statement",
  "Goal & Expectation",
  "User Requirement",
  "Workflow",
  "Data Foundation",
  "Operation & System",
  "Technology & Tool",
  "Control & Safety",
];
---

<section id="how-it-works" class="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="headline">Refine the problem. Define the solution.</h2>
    <p class="intro-text">
      Every product is different. Every business has unique patterns. We don't rush discoveryâ€”we do it right.
    </p>

    <div class="process-facts">
      <span><i class="fas fa-flask"></i> 5-7 Proof of Concepts</span>
      <span><i class="fas fa-users"></i> Real User Validation</span>
      <span><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Time-Based Contract</span>
    </div>

    <div class="methodology">
      <h3>Product Surface Foundation</h3>
      <p class="methodology-desc">
        Everything starts here. Your business patterns, user needs, and technical constraints form the base every layer builds upon. Through communication, we discover each layer:
      </p>

      <div class="layers-list">
        {layers.map((layer, i) => (
          <span class="layer">{layer}</span>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="methodology-note">
        Each layer builds on validated insights, not assumptions. We continue layering discovery until we have a complete picture of what you need.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .how-it-works {
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--space-5xl) var(--space-xl);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: var(--max-width-text);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .headline {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    color: var(--color-cyan-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .intro-text {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .process-facts {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .process-facts span {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  .process-facts i {
    color: var(--color-cyan);
  }

  .methodology h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .methodology-desc {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .layers-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .layer {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-base);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-terracotta);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  .methodology-note {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-cyan);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .how-it-works {
      padding: var(--space-4xl) var(--space-lg);
    }

    .headline {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }

    .process-facts {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>
